  + [created_tool] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\seven_math_problems\proof_inquiry\P_vs_NP_Proof_System_Simulation_Admission_Gate.sop
  + [source_boundary] is local SOP reflection and proof-inquiry tooling only
  + [proof_boundary] is no P equals NP result, no P not equals NP result, and no polynomial refutation theorem

& [GitDiffReflection] is the work evidence
  + [previous_frontier] is proof_system_boundary_ledger
  + [diff_meaning] is the boundary ledger was too broad for a concrete operator claim, so a simulation-specific gate was needed
  + [new_artifact] is proof_system_simulation_admission_gate
  + [scope_control] is tool creation and current application only
  + [unrelated_workspace_changes] are ignored

& [DevelopedUnderstanding] is the research result
  + [old_focus] is whether a coherence or propagation operator solves NP-complete instances
  + [new_focus] is whether failed propagation or repair produces a short checkable refutation in a named proof system
  + [important_distinction] is solution_state_search versus refutation_trace_generation
  + [current_candidate] is local_propagation_with_repair
  + [current_status] is boundary_only
  + [first_missing_feature] is no_polynomial_operator_to_refutation_simulation_for_hard_sat_instances

& [CuriousPeriphery] is the next research edge
  + [subject] is proof traces produced by propagation failures
  + [nearby_theory] is local consistency, resolution/CDCL, cutting planes, polynomial calculus, sum-of-squares, and Frege-like proof systems
  + [question] is whether the candidate operator can emit derivation objects whose size and verification time remain polynomial on hard SAT or NP-complete CSP instances
  + [Deep_Research_Priority_Gate] is not_triggered
    = reason: the current increment clarified the target; external research becomes useful only after a named theorem interface is selected

& [NextBoundedMotion] is the follow-up
  + [mode] is gate_application_or_deep_research_precheck
  + [question] is apply the new gate to local_propagation_with_repair and decide whether a named proof-system theorem should be researched next
  + [expected_output] is either a rejected/admitted scoped row or a Deep_Research_Priority_Gate event for a named proof-complexity interface
